{"parentUuid":"a8b69002-eb73-4bb1-aa28-72ca7dbdc60d","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01NJ5uPNpGje7HTeYWHiRrwP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01BLf5QKicBi6c1Spvogefii","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Answer question about Claude Code conversation context","subagent_type":"claude-code-guide","prompt":"The user is asking: \"How do I load previous conversation context?\" in Claude Code CLI. They want to know how to resume or access a previous conversation session. Please explain the options available in Claude Code for continuing or resuming previous conversations (e.g., --continue, --resume flags, /resume command, etc.). Keep the answer concise and practical."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":111,"cache_read_input_tokens":17526,"output_tokens":171,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":111},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZfczrMyaSgXfYXsGUQo4","type":"assistant","uuid":"223f8996-63ba-40d7-ab22-fad4b021b224","timestamp":"2026-04-02T21:03:21.904Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/home/SparkMe","sessionId":"4a19719b-9960-40ef-9ae3-26c525a0f468","version":"2.1.90","gitBranch":"main","slug":"jolly-chasing-unicorn"}
{"parentUuid":"223f8996-63ba-40d7-ab22-fad4b021b224","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"ef67ca1f-49fa-496a-b4b3-447054ff4a0e","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BLf5QKicBi6c1Spvogefii","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I found the documentation on resuming conversations. Here's how to load previous conversation context in Claude Code CLI:\n\n## Resume Previous Conversations\n\nClaude Code provides several ways to access and resume previous conversations:\n\n**Command-line options:**\n- `claude --continue` — Resume the most recent conversation in your current directory\n- `claude --resume` — Open an interactive session picker to browse and select a conversation (without a session name)\n- `claude --resume <session-name>` — Resume a specific named session directly\n- `claude --from-pr <number>` — Resume a session linked to a pull request\n\n**During an active session:**\n- `/resume` — Switch to a different conversation (opens the picker or lets you type a name)\n\n## Best Practices for Managing Sessions\n\n**Name your sessions for easy recall:**\n```bash\nclaude -n auth-refactor        # Name at startup\n```\n\nOr during a session:\n```\n/rename auth-refactor          # Rename mid-session\n```\n\n**Session picker features** (when using `/resume` or `claude --resume`):\n- Navigate with arrow keys (`↑`/`↓`)\n- Search with `/` to filter sessions\n- Press `R` to rename a session\n- Press `P` to preview before resuming\n- Press `B` to filter sessions by current git branch\n\n## How Session Storage Works\n\n- Sessions are saved locally with full message history per project directory\n- When you resume, all previous context is restored (messages, tool results, conversation state)\n- Sessions are organized by git repository, so they're easy to find among your projects\n- Sessions created with `-p` (headless mode) or SDK invocations don't appear in the picker but can still be resumed with their session ID\n\n**Pro tip:** Get into the habit of naming sessions early with `/rename` when starting distinct tasks—it's much easier to find \"payment-integration\" than \"explain this function\" later."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a5c6b1dd4f4d9373a (use SendMessage with to: 'a5c6b1dd4f4d9373a' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 30684\ntool_uses: 2\nduration_ms: 9913</usage>"}]}]},"uuid":"68d803da-0f31-420d-95f3-f8ac70bbcb65","timestamp":"2026-04-02T21:03:31.935Z","toolUseResult":{"status":"completed","prompt":"The user is asking: \"How do I load previous conversation context?\" in Claude Code CLI. They want to know how to resume or access a previous conversation session. Please explain the options available in Claude Code for continuing or resuming previous conversations (e.g., --continue, --resume flags, /resume command, etc.). Keep the answer concise and practical.","agentId":"a5c6b1dd4f4d9373a","agentType":"claude-code-guide","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I found the documentation on resuming conversations. Here's how to load previous conversation context in Claude Code CLI:\n\n## Resume Previous Conversations\n\nClaude Code provides several ways to access and resume previous conversations:\n\n**Command-line options:**\n- `claude --continue` — Resume the most recent conversation in your current directory\n- `claude --resume` — Open an interactive session picker to browse and select a conversation (without a session name)\n- `claude --resume <session-name>` — Resume a specific named session directly\n- `claude --from-pr <number>` — Resume a session linked to a pull request\n\n**During an active session:**\n- `/resume` — Switch to a different conversation (opens the picker or lets you type a name)\n\n## Best Practices for Managing Sessions\n\n**Name your sessions for easy recall:**\n```bash\nclaude -n auth-refactor        # Name at startup\n```\n\nOr during a session:\n```\n/rename auth-refactor          # Rename mid-session\n```\n\n**Session picker features** (when using `/resume` or `claude --resume`):\n- Navigate with arrow keys (`↑`/`↓`)\n- Search with `/` to filter sessions\n- Press `R` to rename a session\n- Press `P` to preview before resuming\n- Press `B` to filter sessions by current git branch\n\n## How Session Storage Works\n\n- Sessions are saved locally with full message history per project directory\n- When you resume, all previous context is restored (messages, tool results, conversation state)\n- Sessions are organized by git repository, so they're easy to find among your projects\n- Sessions created with `-p` (headless mode) or SDK invocations don't appear in the picker but can still be resumed with their session ID\n\n**Pro tip:** Get into the habit of naming sessions early with `/rename` when starting distinct tasks—it's much easier to find \"payment-integration\" than \"explain this function\" later."}],"totalDurationMs":9913,"totalTokens":30684,"totalToolUseCount":2,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9777,"cache_read_input_tokens":20470,"output_tokens":431,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":9777},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"223f8996-63ba-40d7-ab22-fad4b021b224","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/home/SparkMe","sessionId":"4a19719b-9960-40ef-9ae3-26c525a0f468","version":"2.1.90","gitBranch":"main","slug":"jolly-chasing-unicorn"}
{"parentUuid":"68d803da-0f31-420d-95f3-f8ac70bbcb65","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Kf7yGfvwrMYca76vhPs7m1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here are your options for loading previous conversation context in Claude Code:\n\n## Resuming Previous Conversations\n\n**From the terminal:**\n```bash\nclaude --continue        # Resume the most recent conversation\nclaude --resume          # Open an interactive picker to browse sessions\nclaude --resume <name>   # Resume a specific named session\n```\n\n**Inside an active session:**\n```\n/resume                  # Open the session picker to switch conversations\n```\n\n## Tips\n\n- Use the session picker (`claude --resume`) to navigate with arrow keys, search with `/`, or preview with `P`\n- Name sessions early with `/rename <name>` so they're easy to find later\n- Sessions are scoped per project directory\n\nSince I don't have a saved memory from our last conversation, if you want context to persist across sessions, I can start saving notes to my memory system going forward."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":689,"cache_read_input_tokens":17637,"output_tokens":190,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":689},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZfd1uu5embzAjr8yoAdC","type":"assistant","uuid":"88f63f22-7b69-4623-b2ca-38a41fdac657","timestamp":"2026-04-02T21:03:37.048Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/home/SparkMe","sessionId":"4a19719b-9960-40ef-9ae3-26c525a0f468","version":"2.1.90","gitBranch":"main","slug":"jolly-chasing-unicorn"}
